  <content>&lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Ok, forget about mvvm, that’s not the point of this quick post…&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="/blog/image.axd?picture=image_78.png"&gt;&lt;img style="background-image: none; border-bottom: 0px; border-left: 0px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px; display: inline; border-top: 0px; border-right: 0px; padding-top: 0px" title="image" border="0" alt="image" src="/blog/image.axd?picture=image_thumb_78.png" width="522" height="272" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Have a look at that, ain’t it a thing of beauty!?&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;No more having to get back onto the gui thread, even webforms people have to do it with Control.Invoke    &lt;br /&gt;(or sync context).&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;Parallel task library rocks.&lt;/p&gt;</content>
